abstract: Prosecutors said that Mr. Strauss-Khan admitted to sexual aggression against a writer who interviewed him in 2003 but that it was too late to prosecute him.
snippet: Prosecutors said that Mr. Strauss-Khan admitted to sexual aggression against a writer who interviewed him in 2003 but that it was too late to prosecute him.
lead_paragraph: French prosecutors have dropped an investigation into a claim by a French writer, Tristane Banon, that Dominique Strauss-Kahn tried to rape her during an interview in 2003. The prosecutor's office said on Thursday that Mr. Strauss-Kahn admitted to sexual aggression but that the statue of limitations on that charge had expired. Read more »

headline.main: Case Against Strauss-Kahn Is Dropped in France
